section#competent
  h4.display-4.text-primary
    | Competent Cell Preparation
  p
    | We made 2 competent cells at once: #[i E. coli] \(BL21\) and #[i E. coli] \(DH5α\) with the Sambrook protocol:
  ol
    li prepare overnight pre culture taken from the streak plate of each strain.
    li inoculate 1% of overnight pre-culture to 50mL LB medium.
    li incubate in room temperature ~2.5h up to the OD600 reaches 0.5 - 0.6.
    li divide the broth culture into 2 falcon tubes.
    li centrifuge in 4
      sup o
      | C, 7000rpm in 5 mins.
    li discard the supernatant and keep the pellet in an ice box.
    li add 25mL of pre-chilled 0.1M CaCl#[sub 2] solution and resuspend the cell.
    li incubate for 15 mins in the ice box.
    li centrifuge 4
      sup o
      | C, 7000rpm in 5 mins. discard the supernatant and keep the pellet on ice.
    li add 15mL pre-chilled CaCl#[sub 2] solution and resuspend the pellet.
    li incubate on ice for 15 mins.
    li centrifuge in 4
      sup o
      | C, 7000rpm in 5 min, discard the supernatant and keep the pellet on ice.
    li add 1mL CaCl#[sub 2] + glycerol solution. Resuspend the pellet. Better work in LAF/ BSC.
    li divide the culture into 1.5mL microtube, 60uL each.
    li freeze all tubes using liquid nitrogen.
    li keep in -80
